description:
&lt;p&gt;The Deputy Financial Controller is a key leadership role in the Finance Directorate. The role will provide additional expertise into the Financial Services function, assisting with overseeing and managing the financial transactions, services and core finance systems for the Trust. You will take responsibility for the management of the performance of the financial services team ensuring the delivery of a professional, dynamic, efficient and proactive service to meet the needs of the Trust.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;You will work closely with the team that you will manage and with staff, at all levels, across the Trust to maintain financial control.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are an experienced NHS finance professional wanting to make a real positive difference then we would really like to hear from you.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be a CCAB qualified, or finalist.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Yemisi Oluwa&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title Financial Controller&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address y.oluwa@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 01733 677945&lt;/p&gt;
